It will now be compulsory for every adult Kenyan to make contributions to the national hospital insurance fund should parliament adopt the government-backed national hospital insurance fund amendment bill 2021. the bill proposes to make it mandatory for any person who has attained the age of eighteen years and is not a beneficiary to register as a member of the fund. the bill also proposes to remove the voluntary contribution provision and action that each household pay an annual compulsory 6,000 shillings to facilitate the government&rsquo;s dream of universal health coverage. our senior political reporter Patrick Amimo has the details.